headline: Mastercard Restructuring And Europe Scrutiny Reframe Long Term Growth Story
summary: Mastercard (NYSE:MA) plans to restructure its organization, affecting about 4% of its workforce and resulting in a $200 million charge. The company is revising executive compensation packages to tie leadership pay more closely to long term performance goals. Regulators and policymakers in Europe are increasing scrutiny of US payment networks, including Mastercard, and exploring ways to reduce reliance on them. For you as an investor, this mix of workforce changes, executive pay adjustments,...
